text: was a town located in Tomata District, Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of 2003 (before the merger), the village had an estimated population of 1,732 and a density of 13.24 persons per km². The total area was 130.83 km². On March 1, 2005, Okutsu, along with the villages of Kamisaibara and Tomi (all from Tomata District), was merged into the expanded town of Kagamino. Category:Dissolved municipalities of Okayama Prefecture
title: Okutsu, Okayama
